# Cursor rules for Experiment Hub

> Substantive rules live in `.cursor/rules/` — Cursor loads them automatically by file pattern.
> **Edit rules there.** This file is an index only. Do not duplicate rule content here.

## Rules

**Always-applied (no file trigger):**

- `principles.mdc` — UX/DX balance, test-first, log capture, solo founder practices
- `github-workflow.mdc` — branching (tool/harness prefix + descriptor), PR process
- `figma.mdc` — Figma MCP setup and project-specific design rules

**File-triggered (auto-apply by glob pattern):**

- `commit-messages.mdc` — conventional commit format
- `design-guidelines.mdc` — dark theme, spacing, component patterns
- `component-conventions.mdc` — React component conventions
- `nextjs-api-routes.mdc` — API route conventions
- `vitest-conventions.mdc` — test conventions
- `prd-template.mdc` — experiment PRD format
- `market-research-template.mdc` — market research format

## Skills and agents

Invocable skills and agents live in `skills/` — reference with `@skills/<name>.md` in Cursor:

- `experiment-creator`, `market-research`, `business-case-writer`, `prd-writer` (outcomes + failing tests), `prototype-builder`, `design-advisor`
- `user-communication`, `sitemap` (sitemap: rare; explicit request or Figma sitemap board refresh when IA/routes change)
- `figma/figma-use`, `figma/figma-implement-design`, `figma/figma-generate-design`, and more

See `agents/README.md` for the experiment workflow and approval checkpoints.

## Cursor-specific

- **Figma plugin:** `/add-plugin figma` in agent chat
- **MCP config:** See `.cursor/mcp-config.json.example` for filesystem + experiment-logs setup
